==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Squaw
<hw>Squaw</hw> <pr>(skw⟦add⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Massachusetts
Indian <ets>squa</ets>, <ets>eshqua</ets>; Narragansett
<ets>squ⟦acir⟧ws</ets>; Delaware <ets>ochqueu</ets>, and
<ets>khqueu</ets>; used also in compound words (as the names of animals)
in the sense of <ets>female</ets>.]</ety> <def>A female; a woman,
especially a married woman; a wife; -- in the language of Indian tribes
of the Algonquin family, correlative of <inv>sannup</inv>.</def>
<mark>[Considered offensive by some American indians.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Old squaw</b></col>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <cd>See under
<er>Old</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squawberry</ent>⟦br⟧
